dvance to essential qualities of the discussed works' aesthetic devices and ethical concerns. Questioning conventional interpretive approaches, Markus Schmitz shows what Anglophone Arab studies are and what they can become from a radically decentered relational point of view. Among the writers and artists discussed are such diverse figures as Rabih Alameddine, William Blatty, Kahlil Gibran, Ihab Hassan, Jabra Ibrahim Jabra, Emily Jacir, Walid Raad, Ameen Rihani, Edward Said, Larissa Sansour, and Raja Shehadeh.  afunded by Westfälische Wilhelms-Universität Münster  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnglish literaturexArab authorsxHistory and criticism 0aEnglish literaturexArab influences. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticism. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aBritish Studies. 4aCritical Correlation. 4aCross-cultural (Mis-)Translation. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCulture. 4aIslam. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMiddle Eastern Studies. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aStrategic Lies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAmerican Studies.  aBritish Studies.  aCritical Correlation.  aCross-cultural (Mis-)Translation.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aIslam.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMiddle Eastern Studies.  aPostcolonialism.  aStrategic Lies.2 aWestfälische Wilhelms-Universität Münsterefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMP